The paper deals with the distributed planning of robot trajectories for optimal execution of cooperative tasks, which involves multiple robots working together towards a common goal. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on the planning of robot trajectories, which is a key aspect of Robotics (cs.RO). The paper also uses game theoretic formulations to maximize the collective performance, which suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. The paper also involves planning based on past observations, which suggests that it could belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the consideration of recharging and maintenance needs, which suggests that it could belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category.
